import { FunctionComponent, useState } from "react"; import styles from "./LabRegistrationForm.module.css"; import axios from 'axios'; const SERVER_URL = process.env.REACT_APP_SERVER_URL const GET_URL = SERVER_URL + 'api/my_reservations' export type RootType = { className?: string; }; const LabRegistrationForm: FunctionComponent = ({ className = "", }) => { const [formData, setFormData] = useState({ labName: "", providerGroup: "", providerUnit: "", address: "", state: "", city: "", zipCode: "", officePhone: "", mobile: "", email: "", timeZone: "", }); const [providerGroups, setProviderGroups] = useState([]); const [providerUnits, setProviderUnits] = useState([]); const [timezones, setTimezones] = useState([]); useEffect(() => { axios.get('/api/provider-groups').then(response => setProviderGroups(response.data)); axios.get('/api/provider-units').then(response => setProviderUnits(response.data)); axios.get('/api/timezones').then(response => setTimezones(response.data)); }, []); const handleInputChange = (e: React.ChangeEvent) => { const { name, value } = e.target; setFormData({ ...formData, [name]: value, }); }; const handleSelectChange = (name: string, value: string) => { setFormData({ ...formData, [name]: value, }); }; const handleSubmit = async (e: React.FormEvent) => { e.preventDefault(); try { console.log('form data',formData); const response = await axios.post('http://localhost:3005/api/save', formData); //hard code will replace with .env path console.log('Lab details saved:', response.data); alert('Lab details saved successfully'); } catch (error) { console.error('Error saving lab details:', error); alert('Error saving lab details'); } }; return (
